main event: On November 9, 1956, in Glen Avon, California, a long red object, the size of a dime at arm's length, was observed hovering in one spot for three to four minutes before disappearing. Insufficient data led to no conclusive evaluation, and a meteor was sighted in the same area at the same time.
interesting points: The object was described as long and red, appearing the size of a dime at arm's length.
It hovered in one spot for three to four minutes before disappearing.
The report mentions insufficient data for evaluation, leaving the conclusion inconclusive.
A meteor was sighted in the same area at the same time, suggesting a potential alternative explanation.
The report card is from Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force investigation of unidentified flying objects.
